    <item>
      <title>Geography is more decisive than ideology in choosing a São Paulo city councilor</title>
      <link>/en/blog/camara_sp_2024/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 26 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/en/blog/camara_sp_2024/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/opiniao/2020/09/as-vantagens-da-reeleicao.shtml&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Article published in the &amp;ldquo;Ilustríssima&amp;rdquo; section of &lt;em&gt;Folha de S. Paulo&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, on Oct 26, 2024 (in Portuguese).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An analysis on the 2024 electoral results for the São Paulo city council. I argue that there is a predominance of territorial representation in electoral behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Reelection and municipal elections</title>
      <link>/en/blog/reeleicao_municipal/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/en/blog/reeleicao_municipal/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/voto-a-voto/2024/10/a-reeleicao-e-as-eleicoes-municipais.shtml&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Op-ed published in the &amp;ldquo;Voto a Voto&amp;rdquo; column of &lt;em&gt;Folha de S. Paulo&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, on Oct 4, 2024 (in Portuguese).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I present some historical data regarding reelection in municipal races in Brazil, while discussing theoretical aspects of this phenomenon in the country, in anticipation of the first round of the 2024 elections.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>&#34;Fora da política não há salvação&#34;: Elections across Brazil</title>
